<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by The Singer:
[B]You can twist up to three songs at once. However it's not too effective with three until level 12. Start with two songs at level 6...healing and chant. Then when you get warsong use that and healing. Next when you get anthem use that warsong and healing...you lose it sometimes on a bash but three is better than two. At level 12 Use Bellow, Warsong, and anthem/healing. 
For groups use healing, bellow, and anthem. Now get this...sometimes you have to decide on what ya wanna do. When fighting magic i may use two of the guardian songs. Trust me they really help. And to really confuse you as to what to use..lvl 18 you get a upgraded version the second song. It lowers AC of monsters..i am not sure how much and it does damage. At 20 you get a AC lowering and attack speed lowering also. When Combining these two i have noticed a difference in the creaturs. Be careful because they have a area effect. Bah i am getting long winded! 
Goodbye and good luck

Anavara
Bristlebane Server

P.S. I have a soft spot for young bards so if you see me wave to me and I have been known to Drop the youngins a few plat![/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
